    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA133-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaiviṭai vaittup pirivāṟṟāḷāya talaivi vaṟpuṟukkun tōḻikkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE, who did not have the strength during the separation after the time for the marriage had been fixed, said to [her] confidante who was comforting [her].</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA133">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            tōḷē toṭikoṭ pāṉā kaṇṇē</l>
<l>            vāḷīr vaṭiyiṉ vaṭiviḻan taṉavē</l>
<l>            nutalum pacalai pāyiṉṟu titalaic</l>
<l>            cilpoṟi yaṇinta palkā ḻalkuṉ</l>
<l>            maṇiyē raimpāṉ māyōṭ keṉṟu </l>
<l>            vevvāyp peṇṭir kauvai tūṟṟa</l>
<l>            nāmuṟu tuyarañ ceyyala reṉṉuṅ</l>
<l>            kāmuṟu tōḻi kātalaṅ kiḷavi</l>
<l>            yirumpucey kollaṉ vevvulait teḷitta</l>
<l>            tōymaṭ ciṉṉīr pōla </l>
<l>            nōymali neñciṟ kēmamāñ ciṟitē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The word full of desire [and] love<note place="foot">The syntax of this line is dubious. The commentaries take <term xml:lang="ta">kām-uṟu</term> as an epithet of <term xml:lang="ta">tōḻi</term> which then would have to be read as a antepositioned vocative, a thing fairly rare (except for the <term xml:lang="ta">amma vāḻi</term> variant). I suggest to take it as the first attribute of <term xml:lang="ta">kiḷavi</term>, with a vocative <term xml:lang="ta">tōḻi</term> inserted into the string description.</note>, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">that says “he does not cause the misery we have”,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while hot-mouthed women spread scandal:</l>
<l rend="indent2">“The shoulders! Unending instability of the bracelets. The eyes!</l>
<l rend="indent2">They have lost [their] shape of green mangos cut by a sword<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">vāḷ īr</term>: or "moist in the light".</note>.</l>
<l rend="indent2">Even<note place="foot">T.V.G. reads here a coordination of tōḷē, kaṇṇē, nutalum, with -um only on the last member.</note> the forehead has become pallid</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the dark one with sapphire-like five parts [of hair], [her]</l>
<l rend="indent2">hips with many pearl-strings adorned with few spots of beauty.”</l>
<l>– [it is] small as a protection for the heart abounding in pain,</l>
<l rend="indent3">as a little water touches the earth,</l>
<l rend="indent4">sprinkled on the hot furnace of the iron-working smith.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
